---
import CustomImage from '@/components/CustomImage'
import ImageCarousel from '@/components/ImageCarousel'
import CardCarousel from '@/components/CardCarousel'
import StickyHeader from '@/components/StickyHeader'
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout'

const SITE_TITLE = 'Horizon 80'
---

<BaseLayout title={SITE_TITLE}>
	<StickyHeader
		title='Horizon 80'
		buyUrl='https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3299395184'
		buyLabel='Subscribe on the Workshop'
		exploreLabel='Pride Edition'
		exploreUrl='#pride'
	/>
	<div>
		<h1 class='title text-6xl font-bold'>{SITE_TITLE}</h1>
		<h2 class='text-3xl font-medium mt-4 mb-10'>Star of the Show</h2>
		<CustomImage
			imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/hero.jpg'
			altText='Star of the Show'
		/>
		<div class='flex justify-center mt-10'>
			<div
				class='w-fit px-4 py-1.5 text-sm rounded-full bg-sky-500 hover:bg-sky-600 text-white font-medium transition-colors'
			>
				<a href='https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3299395184' target='_blank'
					>Subscribe on the Workshop</a
				>
			</div>
		</div>

		<article class='prose prose-xl dark:prose-invert w-full max-w-none mt-8'>
			<h2>Horizon 80 - Luxury Travel Trailer</h2>
			<hr />
			<p>
				SentyTek is finally expanding into an amazing sector of vehicle in Stormworks - Campers.
				Stormworkers love to go camping, and the Horizon is our answer to that call. Horizon is our
				lineup of travel trailers, starting with the Horizon 80. It's the best travel trailer camper
				in Stormworks, with enough ease of use and features to bring light to any camping trip.
			</p>
			<CustomImage
				imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/sunset.jpg'
				altText='The Horizon 80, the best travel trailer camper in Stormworks, with a sleek and modern design'
			/>
			<hr />
			<h2>Specs</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Length: 9.0m bumper-to-bumper, 7.0m usable space</li>
				<li>Width: 3.0m Travel mode, 6.25m Camping mode</li>
				<li>Slides: 1</li>
				<li>Sleeping capacity: 4 pax</li>
				<li>Seating capacity: 5 pax</li>
				<li>Weight: 3020 dry, 3040 wet</li>
				<li>Fresh water: 205L</li>
			</ul>
			<hr />
			<h2>Layout</h2>
			<div class='inline-flex'>
				<p><strong>Camping mode:</strong></p>
				<img
					width='50%'
					src='https://i.imgur.com/64Fp2Bw.png'
					alt='Horizon 80 layout in camping mode'
					loading='lazy'
				/>
				<p><strong>Travel mode:</strong></p>
				<img
					width='50%'
					src='https://i.imgur.com/9A5gplj.png'
					alt='Horizon 80 layout in travel mode'
					loading='lazy'
				/>
			</div>
			<hr />
			<h2>Exterior</h2>
			<p>
				Horizon 80 is a full featured travel trailer. With a SiBTaT-compatible connector, Horizon 80
				can connect to any compatible vehicle and function perfectly. A small storage area near the
				lockable, dual-pole door lets campers store essential suitcases, extra welding torches, or
				anything else needed. A small grill and repair cabinet hosts essential equipment like
				first-aid kits for use in a pinch. An awning extends out, providing shade for sunny days. A
				connector on the back lets Horizon connect to the base plate on select vehicles, or tow
				other vehicles itself, creating a toy hauler from a single camper.
			</p>
			<CustomImage
				imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/ext.jpg'
				altText='The rear of the Horizon 80, showing the grill and repair cabinet, and the tow connector'
			/>
			<p>
				A small service port connects the water tanks and electrical connection to a campgrounds
				connectors, to help recharge and refuel the camper. An advanced, first-of-its-kind leveling
				system with 4 jacks is incredibly versatile, allowing campers to level Horizon 80 on almost
				any surface, creating a much more comfortable camping experience. Horizon 80 is also
				SenConnect compatible, letting other SenConnect users see where the camper is, and with
				Private Networks, it's possible to isolate a campsite, and only let other campers know where
				Horizon is.
			</p>
			<hr />
			<h2>Interior</h2>
			<p>
				Horizon's interior is filled with features to make camping a fun experience. The large
				dinette slideout gives a ton of room inside the camper for activities. Every light in
				Horizon 80 is an RGB light, easier on the eyes with smooth fades and rave modes. A small
				kitchen is only for decoration*, including the Solid Rocket Booster in the fridge. A
				flip-down TV has up to 20km of range, and a radio with up to 24km of range. The TV also has
				a cable connection with composite pass through, to connect your favorite games and TV shows
				on cable.
			</p>
			<p>
				A fireplace**, a pair of 110v heaters, a functional seat, 3 openable windows, two separate
				TVs and radios, Horizon 80 is the perfect camper for any situation. Download today.
			</p>
			<ImageCarousel
				images={[
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/int.jpg',
						alt: 'The interior of the Horizon 80, showing the dinette slideout and the kitchen area'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/kitchen.jpg',
						alt: 'The kitchen area of the Horizon 80, showing the appliances and storage options'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/living.jpg',
						alt: 'The living area of the Horizon 80, showing the seating and entertainment options'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/bed.jpg',
						alt: 'The sleeping area of the Horizon 80, showing the bed and storage options'
					}
				]}
			/>
			<CardCarousel>
				<div class='rounded-3xl bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-800 p-8 text-center' id='pride'>
					<ImageCarousel
						images={[
							{
								path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/pride-1.jpg',
								alt: 'Pride Edition hooked up to a RV hookup at a campsite'
							},
							{
								path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/pride-2.jpg',
								alt: 'Pride Edition at a campsite, fishing'
							},
							{
								path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/pride-3.jpg',
								alt: 'Pride Edition with Echolodia TE'
							},
							{
								path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/horizon-80/pride-4.jpg',
								alt: 'Pride Edition at a waterline'
							}
						]}
					/>
					<h4 class='text-xl font-bold mb-2'>Check out Pride Edition</h4>
					<p class='text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300'>
						The Horizon 80 Pride Edition features a custom paint job, with the colors of the pride
						flag, and a custom interior with rainbow accents. Download it for free on the workshop,
						and show your pride on the road!
					</p>
					<a
						href='https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3499419916'
						target='_blank'
						class='inline-block mt-4 px-4 py-2 bg-sky-500 hover:bg-sky-600 text-white font-medium rounded-full transition-colors'
						>Subscribe on the Workshop</a
					>
				</div>
			</CardCarousel>
			<hr />
			<p>
				<strong>Notes:</strong> Horizon 80 tows best with a high powered pickup truck. Do not tow with
				the stabilizers enabled, the parking brake on, the awning open, the slide-out extended, or passengers
				in the vehicle. Do not take turns at high speed while towing Horizon 80. Horizon 80 does not come
				with a generator, and may need one for extended use.
			</p>
			<p>*Kitchen appliances credit to Imagine Wagons.</p>
			<p>**Fireplace credit to Tajin.</p>
		</article>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
	import { animate } from 'motion'
	const showAnimations = localStorage.getItem('animations') === 'true'

	if (showAnimations) {
		animate(
			'.title',
			{ y: [80, 0], opacity: [0, 1] },
			{
				duration: 2.5,
				opacity: { duration: 3 },

				offset: [0, 0.55, 0.75]
			}
		)
	}
</script>
